# Agent Instructions — {{PROJECT_NAME}}

> Canonical development process: **[docs/AGENCY_WORKFLOW.md](docs/AGENCY_WORKFLOW.md)** (single source of truth). Applies to any AI agent working in this repo.

Minimum non-negotiables:
1. Classify the request via the router before acting; don't run heavy workflow for small tasks.
2. Use Plan Mode for paths with Gates before editing.
3. Read only the docs needed for the selected path; avoid loading unrelated context.
4. Do not bypass hooks, checks, or verification.
5. Use GitNexus for Standard/Full impact/context analysis when available.
6. **Sub-agent delegation is path-triggered, not user-prompt-triggered.** For Standard/Full paths and broad brownfield changes, use sub-agents as required by [TEAM_ROSTER](docs/TEAM_ROSTER.md); do not wait for the user to say "use sub-agents".
7. Keep outputs concise: findings, decisions, risks, next steps.
